    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "A couple of comments and I'm going to make some quick edits.\n- Best way to check for None is `obj is None` instead of `obj == None`. The latter will fail on many values of `obj`\n- The fastest way to get the values in a row of a DataFrame is to use `irow`, `xs`, or indexing with `ix`. This function has issues with integer indexes (http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/whatsnew.html#api-changes-to-integer-indexing) that I'm fixing now\n"
